node.text:
A new Colombian Netflix series has been accused by fans of copying some of the iconic art from Grand Theft Auto V loading screens in its opening credits sequence.

Grand Theft Auto fans over on Reddit have started to notice that there are some "suspiciously similar" images in the show's opening moments. Swipe to take a look for yourself 👉

📸 Frandoy / Netflix / Take Two Interactive

node.text:
One GTA fan decided to crash a live TV show in Germany and demand to know where exactly GTA VI is... 👇

The gamer in question, who apparently goes by Taser, stormed the stage of German game show Schlag den Star (Beat The Celebrity) to ask the host, a comedian called Elton, about GTA VI. Maybe Elton's uncle works at Rockstar?

Elton was only able to respond with a nervous shrug. It seems the cast and crew of Schlag den Star know about as much as we do on the subject of GTA VI. Taser was left none the wiser, and was swiftly escorted off the stage by security. 👮‍♂️
